
Sun 17 10:45AM      Started modifying Tok macros to only take one parameter
    There is a discontinuity in that a macro definition allows multiple parameters but a macro invocation only allows one. Since a macro invocation ought not be (and is not) constrained by its parameter, it is not feasible to have multiple parameters because there is no way to easily differentiate parameters when a parameter can be anything. Otherwise the syntax gets ugly.
    Turns out the balance rule for CheckMacroParameters is crapping out. Need to rewrite so plg handling of balance rules will have to be modified
     

